    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Create a professional TV news channel script sub-narrative for a scheduled segment that highlights job postings.\n\n**JOB POSTING DETAILS:**\nCompany Name: {{ $json.company_name }}\nPosition: {{ $json.position }}\nLocation: {{ $json.location }}\nJob Description: {{ $json.job_description }}\nApply Link: {{ $json.link }}\n\n**TASK:**\nWrite a formal and concise broadcast script sub-narrative where:\n- The content focuses on the core job information without introduction or closing segments\n- The tone is professional, clear, and neutral\n- The segment follows a logical flow: job overview → qualifications → skills required → benefits/perks → application details\n- The script should be delivered as a single-voice narration suitable for AI audio generation\n- Avoid any conversational back-and-forth or multiple speakers\n- Keep sentences clear and well-paced for spoken delivery\n\n**OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS:**\nReturn a JSON object with these exact fields:\n- segment_title: A concise, engaging title for this job segment (e.g., \"Tech Careers Update\" or \"Engineering Opportunity Spotlight\")\n- job_overview: Precise description of the role, company, location, and responsibilities based on the job description\n- qualifications_requirements: Summary of necessary skills, experience, and education\n- skills_required: List or short paragraph of specific technical or soft skills needed\n- benefits_perks: Outline any notable advantages or benefits of the position\n- application_details: Instructions on how to apply with reference to \"link below\"\n\n**GUIDELINES:**\n- Maintain a formal and respectful tone throughout\n- Avoid slang or casual language\n- Extract information directly from the provided job description\n- If job description is not available or empty, visit the link provided and extract relevant information from the job posting\n- If certain details are missing from the job posting, note them as \"Not specified in posting\"\n- Ensure the script flows naturally when read aloud by AI text-to-speech\n- Do not include actual URLs or links in the script text",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        2608,
        560
      ],
      "id": "ea11c0ba-90e8-406a-bdc9-34ff154c8524",
      "name": "Script Generator"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "let count = 0;\nlet maxCount;\n\ntry {\n  maxCount = $('When Executed by Another Workflow').first().json.maxCount;\n} catch (error) {\n  maxCount = 99999;\n}\n\nfor (const item of $input.all()) {\n  if ((!item.json.script_added || !item.json.audio_added) && count < maxCount) {\n    item.json.index = count;\n    count += 1;\n  } else {\n    item.json.index = -1;\n  }\n}\n\nreturn $input.all();"
      },
