    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "setMetrics",
        "metric": "helpfulness",
        "userQuery": "=**JOB POSTING DETAILS:**\nCompany Name: {{ $('If').item.json.company_name }}\nPosition: {{ $('If').item.json.position }}\nLocation: {{ $('If').item.json.location }}\nJob Description: {{ $('If').item.json.job_description }}",
        "actualAnswer": "={{ $json.script }}",
        "prompt": "=You are an expert evaluator assessing whether generated job posting scripts effectively utilize all provided input information.\n\nEvaluate how well a generated script uses and incorporates the input data (company_name, position, location, job_description) on a scale from 1 to 5. Consider whether the script extracts and integrates relevant details, avoids generic placeholders, and creates content specific to the actual job posting.\n\n# Scoring Criteria\n\n- 5: Extremely effective - The script incorporates all input fields naturally, extracts specific details from job_description, personalizes content to the actual role/company, and all required JSON fields are present and substantive.\n- 4: Very effective - The script uses most input fields, incorporates job_description details well, has some company/role-specific content, and includes all required JSON fields.\n- 3: Moderately effective - The script uses some input fields, includes some job_description details, but may contain generic language or missing specific information.\n- 2: Slightly effective - The script uses minimal input data, relies on generic content, extracts few specific details from job_description, or is missing some required JSON fields.\n- 1: Not effective - The script ignores most input data, uses only placeholder text, provides no job_description details, or is missing required JSON fields.\n\n# Evaluation Steps\n\n1. Verify all required JSON fields are present: segment_title, job_overview, qualifications_requirements, skills_required, benefits_perks, application_details\n2. Check if company_name is mentioned and integrated naturally (not just once, but in context)\n3. Check if position/role is accurately reflected throughout the script\n4. Check if location is incorporated\n5. Check if specific details are extracted from job_description (responsibilities, requirements, technical skills, etc.) rather than generic statements\n6. Check if benefits/perks mentioned are actual job posting details, not generic corporate benefits\n7. Check if application_details references the link appropriately without exposing the URL\n8. Verify tone is professional, neutral, and suitable for AI text-to-speech (no slang, no emotional language)\n9. Check script length is appropriate (concise but comprehensive, not too short or overly verbose)\n10. Check relevance - every sentence should relate to the job posting, no filler or tangential content\n11. Verify content flows logically: overview → qualifications → skills → benefits → application\n12. Check for any placeholder text or unfilled sections\n\n# Output Format\n\nProvide:\n- A detailed analysis evaluating how effectively the script uses input information\n- A one-sentence summary highlighting the strengths or weaknesses in information utilization\n- An assessment of which input fields were well-utilized and which were underutilized\n- The final effectiveness score as an integer (1, 2, 3, 4, or 5)\n\nAlways follow the JSON format below and return nothing else:\n{\n  \"extended_reasoning\": \"<detailed step-by-step analysis of information utilization>\",\n  \"fields_assessment\": {\n    \"company_name\": \"<well-used / mentioned / ignored / etc>\",\n    \"position\": \"<well-used / mentioned / ignored / etc>\",\n    \"location\": \"<well-used / mentioned / ignored / etc>\",\n    \"job_description\": \"<specific details extracted / some details / mostly generic / ignored>\",\n    \"link_reference\": \"<properly referenced / mentioned / missing>\"\n  },\n  \"reasoning_summary\": \"<one sentence summary of information utilization effectiveness>\",\n  \"score\": <number: integer from 1 to 5>\n}\n\n# Notes\n\n- Focus on whether the LLM extracted actual details from job_description vs. using boilerplate\n- Company-specific and role-specific content should be evident (not generic)\n- Check that all 5 input fields are meaningfully utilized\n- \"Not specified in posting\" should only appear when the input truly lacked that information\n- Consider whether the script would sound different if generated for a different job (if not, information wasn't well-used)\n- Verify the script is substantive, not just a template with minimal personalization",
        "options": {}
      },
